As I read through your post, I thought that this would only really work for a really thick steak. One much thicker than I cook at home. And it turns out that yes, that is the case.   From the looks of it, the steak looks like it was seared really hot.  Is there any true difference between building up that level of brown goodness slowly vs. doing it quickly?<br />
