					<div class='post entry-content '>
						<!--cached-Tue, 22 Feb 2011 03:09:22 +0000-->Uhhhh.<br />
<br />
Perhaps a dumb question but, given the title of &quot;The best way to cook a steak,&quot; yet seeing that the steak must be at least 1 1/2 inches thick, was Prime, dry-aged Lobels, etc. can you really support this claim?<br />
<br />
If this will not work will with 90% of the steaks in the US, how is it the &quot;best&quot; way to cook a steak?<br />
<br />
I think the best way is a quick sear followed by a short trip in a hot oven.<br />
<br />
This works for every steak (if it's a really cheap, supermarket steak, you just skip the trip in the oven).
						
						<br />
						
