					<div class='post entry-content '>
						<!--cached-Tue, 22 Feb 2011 03:09:22 +0000-->What no meat thermometer?<br />
<br />
My guess is the centre as lower, more like 135F; the steak about an inch and a half thick; working backwards assuming ten minutes cooking a side gives a pan surface temperature of about 170F. A pity you did not measure it. &quot;medium heat&quot; covers a wide range.<br />
<br />
Personally I prefer to cook my steak, especially wing rib, sous vide at 55C for 24 hours to let the colalgen dissolve, searing before and after.
						
