<span class='bbc_right'><a href='http://forums.egullet.org/index.php?app=forums&amp;module=forums&amp;section=findpost&amp;pid=1616249' class='bbc_url'><img src='http://forums.egullet.org/public/style_images/egullet/snapback.png' alt='View Post' /></a></span><br /></div></div><br />
<br />
But isn't this method just a reverse derivative of the classic method? Both uses high heat for a short time to brown the surface and gentle heat to cook the steak through. Fat Guy's interpretation of Ducasse's method cooks the steaks for 10 min per side on a 170F pan (jackal10 calculation), which i believe, should the steak have not been so marbled, will yield a area of &quot;greyness&quot;.
						
